---
const notes = [
	{
		label: 'Working style',
		text: 'Start with the big product move, then tighten the system and the implementation until the page feels inevitable.',
	},
	{
		label: 'What I care about',
		text: 'Clarity, motion restraint, and interfaces with enough personality to feel memorable without getting noisy.',
	},
];
---

<section
	id="about"
	class="relative isolate overflow-hidden rounded-[2.5rem] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] px-6 py-8 scroll-mt-28 sm:px-8 sm:py-10 lg:px-10 lg:py-12"
	style="background-color: var(--surface-section); box-shadow: var(--shadow-section);"
	data-animate="fade-up"
	aria-labelledby="about-heading"
>
	<div aria-hidden="true" class="absolute inset-0">
		<div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-image: var(--gradient-section);"></div>
		<div
			class="absolute inset-0"
			style="background-image: radial-gradient(circle at 18% 22%, var(--accent-wash-soft), transparent 26%), radial-gradient(circle at 82% 18%, var(--accent-glow-soft), transparent 22%);"
		></div>
		<div class="absolute inset-x-0 top-0 h-px" style="background-image: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--divider-accent), transparent);"></div>
		<div class="absolute inset-y-10 right-[34%] hidden w-px lg:block" style="background-image: linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, var(--line-soft), transparent);"></div>
	</div>

	<div class="relative z-10 grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(18rem,0.72fr)] lg:items-center">
		<div class="space-y-6">
			<div class="space-y-4">
				<p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.32em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
					About
				</p>
				<h2
					id="about-heading"
					class="max-w-3xl text-3xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.04em] text-[color:var(--color-text)] sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl"
				>
					I like shaping product direction and front-end craft in the same pass.
				</h2>
				<p class="max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-[color:var(--color-text)] sm:text-base">
					My process usually starts with finding the clearest story in the room: what matters,
					where attention should go, and which details earn their keep.
				</p>
				<p class="max-w-2xl text-sm leading-7 text-[color:var(--color-muted-text)] sm:text-base">
					From there I build the system, tune the motion, and keep refining until the final
					interface feels considered in both the design file and the shipped code.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="grid gap-3 sm:grid-cols-2">
				{
					notes.map(({ label, text }) => (
						<div class="rounded-[1.4rem] border border-[color:var(--color-border)] bg-[color:var(--surface-subtle)] px-4 py-4">
							<p class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
								{label}
							</p>
							<p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-[color:var(--color-text)]">{text}</p>
						</div>
					))
				}
			</div>
		</div>

		<div aria-hidden="true" class="flex justify-center lg:justify-end">
			<div class="relative aspect-square w-full max-w-[20rem]">
				<div
					class="absolute inset-0 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--border-accent-soft)]"
					style="background-image: var(--gradient-orb); box-shadow: var(--shadow-orb);"
				></div>
				<div class="absolute inset-4 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--ornament-ring)]"></div>
				<div class="absolute inset-10 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--color-border)] bg-[color:var(--surface-tag)] backdrop-blur-sm"></div>
				<div class="absolute inset-0 flex items-center justify-center">
					<div
						class="rounded-full border border-[color:var(--color-border)] bg-[color:var(--surface-nav)] px-10 py-12 text-center"
						style="box-shadow: var(--shadow-float);"
					>
						<p class="text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.32em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
							Profile Mark
						</p>
						<p class="mt-4 text-5xl font-semibold tracking-[-0.06em] text-[color:var(--color-text)] sm:text-6xl">
							IM
						</p>
						<p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-6 text-[color:var(--color-muted-text)]">
							Product direction, interface systems, and front-end craft carried through with the same level of care.
						</p>
					</div>
				</div>
				<div class="absolute bottom-4 right-2 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--color-border)] bg-[color:var(--surface-soft)] px-4 py-2 text-[0.68rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
					Insu Mun
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>
